'''活章魚'''（{{lang-ko|산낙지}}；{{lang-en|San-nakji}}）是[[朝鮮半島|朝鮮半島]]的一種特殊傳統料理，为用[[長腕小章魚|長腕小章魚]]制作的[[膾_(韓國)|膾]]菜（生食）。長腕小章魚是在韩国被称为nakji的一种小型章鱼物种，由于其尺寸较[[北太平洋巨型章魚|巨型章鱼]]较小，有时也被译成“章鱼宝宝”。<ref name="SKLD">{{Cite web|url=http://stdweb2.korean.go.kr/search/View.jsp?idx=11991|title=san-nakji|website={{tsl|en|Standard Korean Language Dictionary}}|publisher=[[韓國國立國語院|韓國國立國語院]]|language=ko|script-title=ko:산낙지|access-date=22 February 2017|archive-date=2017-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903075355/http://stdweb2.korean.go.kr/search/View.jsp?idx=11991|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种章鱼常被宰杀后切成小块，然后送上餐桌。伴随章鱼触须中的神经活动，其小块在死后仍会在餐盘上运动。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/queens/korean-restaurant-live-octopus-dish-animal-rights-activists-squirming-article-1.444306|title=Korean restaurant's live Octopus dish has animal rights activists squirming|last=Rosen|first=Daniel Edward|date=4 May 2010|work=[[紐約每日新聞|紐約每日新聞]]|access-date=3 June 2017|archive-date=2019-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211222854/https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/queens/korean-restaurant-live-octopus-dish-animal-rights-activists-squirming-article-1.444306|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/biz/2017/05/123_65910.html|title=Clash of culture? Sannakji angers US animal activists|last=Han|first=Jane|date=14 May 2010|work=[[韓國時報|韓國時報]]|access-date=4 June 2017|archive-date=2019-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220102536/http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/biz/2017/05/123_65910.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://munchies.vice.com/en_us/article/eating-a-live-octopus-wasnt-nearly-as-difficult-as-it-sounds|title=Eating a Live Octopus Wasn't Nearly as Difficult As It Sounds|last=Compton|first=Natalie B.|date=17 June 2016|work=Munchies|access-date=4 June 2017|publisher=[[Vice传媒有限公司|VICE]]}}</ref>章鱼有高度复杂的[[神经系统|神经系统]]，其[[神经元|神经元]]的三分之二位于其手臂的神经索中，这使章鱼在即使没有大脑的神经信号输入时也持续表现出各种各样的神经[[反射_(生理学)|反射]]行为。<ref>{{cite journal|year=2012|title=An Embodied View of Octopus Neurobiology|journal=Current Biology|volume=22|issue=20|pages=R887–R892|doi=10.1016/j.cub.2012.09.001|pmid=23098601|author=Hochner, B.}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last2=Sagiv-Zohar|first2=R.|last3=Aharonov|first3=R.|last4=Engel|first4=Y.|last5=Hochner|first5=B.|last6=Flash|first6=T.|year=2005|title=Dynamic model of the octopus arm. I. Biomechanics of the octopus reaching movement|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-neurophysiology_2005-08_94_2/page/1443|journal=J. Neurophysiol.|volume=94|issue=2|pages=1443–58|doi=10.1152/jn.00684.2004|pmid=15829594|first1=Y.|last1=Yekutieli}}</ref>一种不太常见的吃法是直接吃掉整个活的章鱼。<ref>{{Citation|title=Eating Live Octopus|url=https://video.nationalgeographic.com/video/skorea-liveoctopus-pp|accessdate=2018-01-13|archive-date=2018-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180113150226/https://video.nationalgeographic.com/video/skorea-liveoctopus-pp|dead-url=no}}</ref>该菜肴会撒上[[芝麻油|芝麻油]]和烤过的[[芝麻|芝麻]]。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/wordofmouth/2015/jan/30/noma-live-prawn-dish-japan-truth|title=The truth about Noma's live prawn dish|last=Warwick|first=Joe|date=30 January 2015|work=[[衛報|衛報]]|access-date=3 June 2017|archive-date=2017-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826120710/https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/wordofmouth/2015/jan/30/noma-live-prawn-dish-japan-truth|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==食用==
由于该菜肴上桌时，章鱼的吸盘仍然活跃，所以食用活章魚时应特别当心，活动的吸盘可能使它黏在[[口腔|口腔]]或[[咽喉|咽喉]]上。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/food/food-features/Eight-controversial-foods-from-around-the-world/articleshow/47564867.cms|title=Eight controversial foods from around the world|work=The Times of India|accessdate=2019-04-23|archive-date=2016-09-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901081030/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/food/food-features/Eight-controversial-foods-from-around-the-world/articleshow/47564867.cms|dead-url=no}}</ref>这对于部分人群存在[[窒息|窒息]]风险，醉酒者更甚。

==语言差异==
{{tsl|en|North–South differences in the Korean language||南北韓两地}}对“nakji”一词的用法有所不同：南韓用来称[[長腕小章魚|長腕小章魚]]，而北韓用来称[[管魷目|管魷目]]。

==流行==
韓式活章魚会在提供切片生鱼的[[韓國料理|韓國料理]]中提供，但也可以在酒吧中找到，作为伴酒精饮料（如[[韩国烧酒|韩国烧酒]]）的零食。

==健康危害==
食用韓式活章魚有潜在的[[異物阻塞呼吸道|窒息风险]]。由于头足类动物的四肢含有[[神经元|神经元]]，其肢体会继续运动，并且触须上的吸盘保持有抓握力，它可能附着在人的咽喉上，哪怕其身体已被切除且配以芝麻油烹饪<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cntraveler.com/galleries/2014-03-19/most-dangerous-foods|title=The Most Dangerous Foods in the World|work=Condé Nast Traveler|access-date=2018-01-18|language=en|archive-date=2018-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118182202/https://www.cntraveler.com/galleries/2014-03-19/most-dangerous-foods|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有多起因食用韓式活章魚导致窒息的案例。<ref>[[韓國聯合通訊社|韓國聯合通訊社]] 2008-01-21  [http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=001&aid=0001931575 광주서 산낙지 먹다 기도막힌 사고 잇따라] {{Wayback|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=001&aid=0001931575 |date=20190410174527 }}</ref>

